        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Type 1 autoimmune pancreatitis is a form of autoimmune pancreatitis seen in elderly males (>60 years) and presenting with abdominal pain steatorrhea obstructive jaundice and other organ (bile duct kidneys and retroperitoneum) involvement. It is thought to be due to an immunoglobulin G4 (IgG4)-associated systemic disease."
